cs.NI, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.LG

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on network localization and navigation using ultra-wideband sensing and communication technology. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper mentions applications in autonomous driving and smart cities. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possibility as the paper discusses the design and performance characterization of the Peregrine system. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a potential category as the paper mentions the use of algorithms for localization and network operation. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a possibility as the paper discusses the use of spatial and temporal cooperation for localization.
